<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The stock market crash of 1929 led to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Immediate government intervention</option>
            <option letter="b">Widespread bank failures and unemployment</option>
            <option letter="c">Economic recovery</option>
            <option letter="d">International prosperity</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 1929 stock market crash led to widespread bank failures and unemployment as part of a chain reaction throughout the economy. The collapse in stock values triggered bank failures as loans went unpaid, businesses closing due to lack of capital, and a general loss of confidence in the economic system. These cascading effects helped transform the crash into the Great Depression.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
